  "body": "\r\nHyperkube supports a number of short aliases for commands, such as `apiserver`, `controller-manager`, `proxy`, `scheduler`, etc, rather than the longer `kube-apiserver`, `kube-controller-manager`, `kube-proxy`, `kube-scheduler` etc.\r\n\r\nThere are comments indicating this is \"unfortunate\"\r\nhttps://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/blob/ef195428a0c5b16e3f3621b7fe59fa151ca28929/cmd/hyperkube/main.go#L90-L94\r\n\r\nand we still currently create these aliases in the hyperkube docker image:\r\nhttps://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/blob/ef195428a0c5b16e3f3621b7fe59fa151ca28929/cluster/images/hyperkube/Dockerfile#L17-L29\r\n\r\nIt'd be nice to simplify this, assuming we can find all uses of the short aliases and remove them.\r\n\r\n/kind cleanup\r\n\r\nNot sure which sig should own this, so tagging a few.\r\n/sig architecture cluster-lifecycle cli\r\n\r\ncc @luxas @mikedanese",
